title: poonasor
author: poonasor
content: I have 2 GekkoScience Compac F both with  found 0 chip(s)I'm currently testing on windows 11 on cgminerI've updated the drivers using Zadig.Windows recognizes the usb sticksThe lights are on on the sticks but still says found 0 chip(s)I don't have anything special in my .bat file:--suggest-diff 442 --gekko-compacf-freq 100any ideas or suggestions?are these sticks just dead now?thanks

comments.author: os2sam
comments.body: Here's the support thread for the Compac F's:https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=5355470.msg57735149#msg57735149

comments.author: BitMaxz
comments.body: Since Windows 11 is pretty new I never heard of someone yet running Compac F successfully with this OS but would you mind to try all possible solutions from Kano?Check the troubleshooting guide here https://kano.is/gekko.php#trfIf still does not work then try to switch to Linux OS.
